night by refusing to attend, Trump's visit to  Atlanta is expected to dominate headlines again,  

13
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:01,740
with his arrival expected to coincide with  evening prime time television viewing hours.

14
00:01:01,740 --> 00:01:04,440
"For NPR News, I'm Stephen Fowler, in Atlanta."

15
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:09,240
One high school fully re- or opens  today in the Maui town of Lahaina,  

16
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:14,400
where at least 115 people died in a  wildfire earlier this month. Meanwhile,  

17
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:19,860
NPR's Jennifer Ludden reports more places  are offering temporary housing to survivors:

18
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:25,560
"In addition to hotels, the county says landlords  and property owners across the state have stepped  

19
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:32,160
up — they've offered 900 houses, apartments  or rooms for wildfire survivors to rent. A new  

20
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:37,200
Maui bus route also starts Thursday; it will  take evacuees between hotels and a shopping  

21
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:41,400
