40
00:03:03,780 --> 00:03:09,360
Republican presidential hopefuls gathered in  Milwaukee for the first Republican presidential  

41
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:14,640
primary debate carried by the Fox News  Channel. They sparred over a number of issues,  

42
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:19,620
including the economy, abortion and former  President Donald Trump's alleged efforts  

43
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:23,820
to overturn the 2020 election.  NPR's Sarah McCammon has more:

44
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:28,620
"Trump refused to attend the debate, saying  his solid lead in primary polls made his  

45
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:33,420
participation unnecessary. Moderators asked  the candidates to weigh in on indictments  

46
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:36,960
he's facing in four jurisdictions  and his actions leading up to the  

47
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:41,220
January 6th Insurrection. Former Vice  President Mike Pence said in a debate  

48
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:45,480
on the Fox News Channel he would support  Trump if he's the Republican nominee,  

49
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:50,640
even if he's convicted, but Pence said he could  not support Trump's request on January 6th:

50
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:57,420
'He asked me to put him over the Constitution,  and I chose the Constitution — and I always will.'

51
00:03:57,420 --> 00:04:02,340
"Eight Republicans met the criteria to participate  in the Milwaukee debate, which includes signing a  

52
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:07,620
pledge to support the eventual nominee. The city  also will host the GOP convention next summer.

53
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:10,020
"Sarah McCammon, NPR News, Milwaukee."

54
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:15,360
I'm Jeanine Herbst, and you're  listening to NPR News, from Washington.